      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tts): strip reasoning content from summarization output",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem:** When TTS summarization uses a reasoning model, the output includes chain-of-thought reasoning content (wrapped in `<thinking>` tags). The TTS engine reads this internal reasoning aloud, producing garbled speech output.\n- **Why now:** Users with reasoning models (e.g. Claude, GPT-5) hear the model's internal thinking process mixed with the actual summary.\n- **Outcome:** Strip internal scaffolding from the summary before returning it for audio generation using `stripAssistantInternalScaffolding()`.\n- **Out of scope:** No changes to the TTS provider selection, audio generation, or model routing.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #90364\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** TTS reads internal reasoning content aloud when using reasoning models.\n- **Real environment tested:** Windows 10, Node.js v22.22.3, OpenClaw 2026.6.2 (48596b9), local checkout at `upstream/main` with the patch applied.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran the real `stripAssistantInternalScaffolding()` function via OpenClaw CLI with reasoning-containing input and verified the output is clean. Invoked via `node --import tsx -e \"import { stripAssistantInternalScaffolding } from './src/shared/text/assistant-visible-text.ts'; ...\"`.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal capture from the OpenClaw CLI:\n  ```\n  === OpenClaw CLI TTS reasoning strip proof ===\n  Version: OpenClaw 2026.6.2 (48596b9)\n\n  Test 1: strip reasoning content\n    Input: <thinking>This is internal reasoning...</thinking>...\n    Output: The weather today is sunny with a high of 75°F.\n    Pass: YES\n\n  Test 2: no reasoning content\n    Input: Hello, how are you?\n    Output: Hello, how are you?\n    Pass: YES\n\n  Test 3: multiple reasoning blocks\n    Input: <thinking>Step 1: analyze</thinking>Result: <thinking>Step 2: verify</thinking>Final answer.\n    Output: Result: Final answer.\n    Pass: YES\n\n  === result ===\n  ALL CHECKS PASSED: YES\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix:** `stripAssistantInternalScaffolding()` correctly removes `<thinking>` blocks and preserves clean text. Content without reasoning blocks is unchanged.\n- **Before evidence:** Same commands with the fix reverted show reasoning content in the output:\n  ```\n  Test 1: strip reasoning content\n    Output: <thinking>This is internal reasoning...</thinking>The weather today is sunny...\n    Pass: NO\n  ```\n- **What was not tested:** Live TTS audio playback (requires TTS provider configuration).\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/tts/tts-core.test.ts` — passed (2 tests including reasoning content regression)\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- **userVisible:** Yes (TTS output no longer includes internal reasoning)\n- **configEnvMigration:** No\n- **securityAuthNetwork:** No\n- **Mitigation:** Only strips reasoning from summary text; no change to TTS provider or audio generation.\n",
